"{\"uid\": \"thenorthlines.com-manu-becomes-first-indian-woman-shooter-to-win-olympic-medal-with-10m-air-pistol-bronze\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"CHATEAUROUX (FRANCE), Jul 28: A resilient Manu Bhaker became the first Indian woman shooter to claim an Olympic medal by snaring a bronze in the 10m air pistol event here on Sunday, a triumph that opened the country's account in the Paris Games and ended a 12-year wait for its much-hyped shooters.The last time India won shooting medals at the Olympics was in 2012 London edition where rapid-fire pistol shooter Vijay Kumar and 10m air rifle marksman Gagan Narang clinched silver and bronze respectively.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 42, \"end\": 53, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manu Bhaker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\"}, {\"begin\": 71, \"end\": 77, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.9935461327016784, \"rank\": 0.006478492464611783, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9990447282897206, \"rank\": 0.00038176797902749165, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999445208, \"rank\": 5.012959661389898e-11, \"text\": \"2012 London\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 413, \"en